  "glottolog_code": "basq1248",
  "notes": "Standard Basque (Euskara Batua), codified by the Royal Academy of the Basque Language (Euskaltzaindia) from 1968. Notable for apical/laminal sibilant contrast (/s̺/ vs /s̻/) and three affricate series (ts̻, ts̺, tʃ). Dialectal variation across the six historical dialects is extensive; Batua draws primarily from Gipuzkoan and Lapurdian sources. Basque is a language isolate with no demonstrated genetic relationship to any other language family.",
